description.description_en: Perennial herbs with horizontal rhizomes.Leaves centrally peltate, margins entire or slightly wavy, circular, 20-60 cm in diameter, pale green to green, glabrous above, green beneath; petioles 1-2 m long, short spined.Flowers showy, solitary, 10-25 cm across, fragrant; peduncle 1-2 m long, sepals 4 or 5, caducous; petals many, broadly elliptic, concave, white or pink; stamens numerous.Fruit aggregate, embedded in an enlarged receptacle, ellipsoid or ovoid, 1-1.7 cm long, the top protruding, reddish-brown.
